  "prompt": "What do people like watching on YouTube?",
  "response": "People enjoy a wide variety of content on YouTube, reflecting the platform's diverse user base and the wide range of interests. Popular categories include:\n\n1. **Entertainment**: This includes music videos, comedy sketches, web series, and movie trailers. Channels like PewDiePie and T-Series have massive followings.\n\n2. **Gaming**: Gamers love watching playthroughs, live streams, game reviews, and tutorials. Popular gaming channels include Markiplier, Jacksepticeye, and Ninja.\n\n3. **Vlogs**: Daily or weekly video blogs where creators share aspects of their lives. Popular vloggers include Casey Neistat and David Dobrik.\n\n4. **Educational Content**: Tutorials, how-to guides, and explainer videos on a variety of topics, from coding to cooking to science. Channels like Khan Academy, TED-Ed, and Vsauce are well-liked.\n\n5. **Beauty and Fashion**: Makeup tutorials, product reviews, fashion hauls, and skincare routines. Influencers like Jeffree Star and Zoella have large audiences.\n\n6. **DIY and Crafts**: Step-by-step guides on creating projects at home, from home decor to art. Channels like 5-Minute Crafts are popular.\n\n7. **Technology**: Reviews, unboxings, and news about the latest gadgets and tech trends. Popular tech reviewers include Marques Brownlee and Linus Tech Tips.\n\n8. **Fitness and Health**: Workout routines, nutrition advice, and wellness tips. Channels like Blogilates and Athlean-X have substantial followings.\n\n9. **Food and Cooking**: Recipes, cooking techniques, and food reviews. Channels like Tasty and Bon App\u00e9tit are favorites.\n\n10. **Travel**: Travel vlogs, destination guides, and adventure videos. Creators like Drew Binsky and Kara and Nate capture the interest of travel enthusiasts.\n\n11. **Documentaries and Analysis**: In-depth explorations of various topics, including history, science, and social issues. Channels like Kurzgesagt \u2013 In a Nutshell and Vox are popular.\n\n12. **Sports**: Highlights, analysis, and commentary on various sports. Channels like ESPN and Dude Perfect attract many viewers.\n\n13. **ASMR**: Videos designed to stimulate a tingling sensation for relaxation. Channels like Gibi ASMR and ASMR Darling are popular in this niche.\n\nUltimately, what people like to watch on YouTube can depend on their individual interests, but these categories tend to have broad appeal and large audiences.",
